        "body": "Summary\n- Adds doctor legacy-state imports for Telegram bot-info and forum topic-name cache sidecars into plugin KV state.\n- Allows plugin-state imports with an empty scope key so caches whose namespace already encodes scope keep exact runtime keys.\n- Adds regressions for both Telegram sidecars and unscoped plugin-state imports.\n\nVerification\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/telegram/src/state-migrations.test.ts src/commands/doctor-state-migrations.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/bot-info-cache.test.ts extensions/telegram/src/topic-name-cache.test.ts\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.extensions.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/telegram-legacy-migrations-extensions.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.extensions.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/telegram-legacy-migrations-extensions-test.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p tsconfig.core.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/telegram-legacy-migrations-core.tsbuildinfo\n- node scripts/run-tsgo.mjs -p test/tsconfig/tsconfig.core.test.json --incremental --tsBuildInfoFile .artifacts/tsgo-cache/telegram-legacy-migrations-core-test.tsbuildinfo\n- git diff --check\n- .agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local\n\nBehavior addressed: Telegram legacy bot-info and forum topic-name sidecar caches from before PR #86027 are now imported into plugin KV state instead of being silently ignored.\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on Linux.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: targeted Vitest migration/cache tests plus extension/core tsgo lanes listed above.\nEvidence after fix: tests assert bot-info sidecars import account-keyed entries, topic-name sidecars import exact chat/thread keys, and unscoped plugin-state imports archive after exact-key migration.\nObserved result after fix: all listed checks passed after rebasing onto latest origin/main.\nWhat was not tested: live Telegram E2E, because this fix is offline legacy state migration rather than send/receive runtime behavior.",
